@startuml
title Compact Rebuild Pipeline

skinparam backgroundColor #F7F1E6
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 135
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam nodesep 26
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 15
skinparam TitleFontSize 20
skinparam NoteFontSize 14
skinparam ArrowFontSize 13
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #1D1D1D
skinparam RectangleBackgroundColor #F2E9D9
skinparam RectangleFontColor #161616
skinparam RectangleRoundCorner 10
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}

top to bottom direction

rectangle "Strip images /\nreinjected attachments" as strip #E8DDD0
rectangle "Summarize" as summarize #F2E9D9
rectangle "Compact request PTL?" as ptl #F5EBDD
rectangle "Retry with\ntruncated head" as retry #F5EBDD
rectangle "Build compact\nboundary" as boundary #EFE6D8
rectangle "Reinject files / plan /\nskills / tool deltas / MCP" as reinject #EFE6D8
rectangle "Post-compact\nworking context" as post #E8DDD0

strip --> summarize
summarize --> ptl
ptl --> retry : yes
ptl --> boundary : no
retry --> boundary
boundary --> reinject
reinject --> post

note right of post
The goal of compact is not
to produce one neat summary.
It is to rebuild the semantic
floor that lets the next turn
keep working.
end note

@enduml
